The paper deals with graph algorithms and parameterized complexity, which are topics that are commonly found in the computer science sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The focus on treewidth and minor-free graphs suggests that cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DM and cs.GT. The mention of kernelization and single-exponential algorithms also points towards cs.CC.
